<article id="post-14612" class="post-14612 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-productivity tag-google-calendar tag-james-clear tag-productivity-2 tag-system tag-todoist">
	
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/11/28/one-small-system-that-kept-me-steady-this-week/" rel="bookmark">One small system that kept me steady this week</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		
<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="750" height="500" src="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/calm-room.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-14613" srcset="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/calm-room.jpg 750w, https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/calm-room-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><em>Photo: Curated lifestyle from Unsplash+</em></figcaption></figure>



<p>This week has not gone to plan. I’ve been unwell, work has been busy, and life has thrown a few unexpected challenges my way. A younger version of me would have tried to push through, hold everything in my head, and hope for the best. That approach never worked for me.</p>



<p>One thing that kept me steady was something very simple: my system kept working, even when I couldn’t.</p>



 <a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/11/28/one-small-system-that-kept-me-steady-this-week/#more-14612" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">One small system that kept me steady this week</span></a>	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	
