<article id="post-14560" class="post-14560 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-agile tag-agile tag-single-responsibility-principle tag-solid tag-srp tag-user-story">
	
	<a class="post-thumbnail" href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/09/21/should-agile-user-stories-follow-the-single-responsibility-principle/" aria-hidden="true">
		<img width="750" height="500" src="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fork-in-the-road.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="Should agile user stories follow the Single Responsibility Principle?" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fork-in-the-road.jpg 750w, https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/fork-in-the-road-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" />	</a>

		
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/09/21/should-agile-user-stories-follow-the-single-responsibility-principle/" rel="bookmark">Should agile user stories follow the Single Responsibility Principle?</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		
<p>A few years ago, I was chatting with a senior developer about Robert C. &#8216;Uncle Bob&#8217; Martin and the Single Responsibility Principle (SRP). It struck me that the principle might not just apply to software design, but could also be a useful way to think about writing agile user stories.</p>



<p>So I’ve been sitting with the question: should user stories follow the Single Responsibility Principle too?</p>



 <a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/09/21/should-agile-user-stories-follow-the-single-responsibility-principle/#more-14560" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="screen-reader-text">Should agile user stories follow the Single Responsibility Principle?</span></a>	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	
	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/09/21/should-agile-user-stories-follow-the-single-responsibility-principle/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-09-21T15:46:29+01:00">Sunday 21 September 2025</time><time class="updated" datetime="2025-09-21T15:47:44+01:00">Sunday 21 September 2025</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/category/agile/" rel="category tag">Agile</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/tag/agile/" rel="tag">Agile</a>, <a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/tag/single-responsibility-principle/" rel="tag">single responsibility principle</a>, <a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/tag/solid/" rel="tag">solid</a>, <a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/tag/srp/" rel="tag">srp</a>, <a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/tag/user-story/" rel="tag">user story</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/09/21/should-agile-user-stories-follow-the-single-responsibility-principle/#respond">Leave a comment<span class="screen-reader-text"> on Should agile user stories follow the Single Responsibility Principle?</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->

