<article id="post-14541" class="post-14541 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-music tag-brent-hinds tag-death tag-mastodon">
	
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.garethjmsaunders.co.uk/2025/08/26/rip-brent-hinds-1974-2025/" rel="bookmark">RIP Brent Hinds (1974–2025)</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		
<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Mastodon - Toe to Toes [In-Studio Performance]" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/HDjKC_DjsWo?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div></figure>



<p>For the last few days, I&#8217;ve been reeling at the news of the <a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/cp8968vdlp0o">sudden and untimely death</a> of former Mastodon guitarist and co-vocalist William Brent Hinds.</p>



<p>By all accounts, he was a force of nature. A wild character. And a fabulously inventive guitarist and vocalist. I feel thankful that I have stood in the same room as him on a couple of occasions and marvelled at Mastodon&#8217;s unique brand of rock n&#8217; roll.</p>



<p>When big characters who have burned so brightly in life are suddenly and cruelly extinguished, life suddenly feels fragile. But now is the time to rage against that darkness and live life to the full. This week I have been doing that to soundtrack of Mastodon.</p>



<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-layout-flow wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow">
<p>There&#8217;s an open wound placed upon my heart in anger&#8217;s rage<br>If we open up a spirit, it&#8217;s a spirit that can bleed</p>



<p>— &#8220;Seabeast&#8221;, Mastodon from Leviathan (2004)</p>
</blockquote>



<p>Sending love and condolences to his family and friends.</p>



<p>Rest in peace, Brent Hinds.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	
